    images: [
      'https://khtunrybrzntlnowlahb.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/artworks/130afdb8-1f02-45ce-89db-e7d15522d2b9/y9bdodpdge_1771040084426__original.webp',
    ],
    shopUrl: 'https://koreasmartcoop.cafe24.com/surl/O/446',
    title_en: 'Sanctuary of Prayer',
    description_en:
      'My work speaks of landscapes of refuge. The Sanctuary of Yearning series carries the feelings of recollection, hope, and purification. I see yearning (念願) as a latent energy, a primal force that draws toward the moment of healing, and I explore that force in the language of painting. I have named the journey of accumulating good karma and reaching liberation through the power of yearning "Karmadise."\nThe wishes within the heart linger in the sanctuary of yearning, are purified there, and once again move toward the light. I bring the time of recovery into painting, and as one passes through that place and returns to life, one gains a new breath. I express a space of protection in which one can quietly catch one\'s breath between unsteady, wavering feelings and the wishes one longs to reach. The repeating forms and the rhythm of flowing lines visualize the faint vibration of hope within inner chaos, and I call this a "shamanic sanctuary." This goes beyond simple expression — it carries a sacred force that liberates the inner self and revives vitality.\nThe motifs in the work are made up of metaphorical symbols of healing. Tangled threads appear as healing threads stitching up the wounds born from memories of my late father, and the layered brushwork represents accumulated memory and the process of practice. Drawing on Didier Anzieu\'s concept of the "psychic envelope (Psychic Envelope)," I tried to embody an inner protective skin that wraps around like our outer skin. My work, where skeins of thread combine with shamanic symbols, makes visible the power held in the form of belief, and the canvas is transformed into a refined sacred object that filters out negative energies.\nUsing oil paint and fluorescent pigments, I stage a visual paradise that glows under light, painting ideal worlds such as "Sanctuary of Yearning," "Guardian Tree," and "Lucid Dream." For me, art is a single ray of light in a dark world, and life itself. As a landscape of the unconscious and a space of protection, I pray that it may quiet anxious states of mind and that everyone may meet a moment in which they can breathe.',
