    title_en: 'Nude',
    description_en:
      'Kim Nam-Jin (金南鎭) was born in 1957 in Gongju, Chungcheongnam-do, and graduated from Korea University.\nHe held the solo exhibition Nights in Itaewon at Pine Hill Gallery in 1987, and Polaroid Nudes at Batanggol Art Hall in 1993.\nHis Nights in Itaewon documentary series, begun in 1984, is regarded as one of the successful experiments in indigenous form within Korean photography.\nHe then experimented with new modes of nude photography using image transfer of Polaroid color, and from 1987 he ran the Kim Nam-Jin Photography Studio (sajin gongbang), systematizing for a Korean readership the various tendencies, theory, and aesthetics of contemporary photography and training many younger photographers.\nAs an exhibition curator, he has organized and run the Seoul International Photo Festival and the Chungmuro Photo Festival, and currently serves as the head of the Photography Culture Forum and Gallery Bresson.',
    artist_en: 'Kim Namjin',
