      "- Wind and Light\nTime traces back, far past the present, into a distant memory.\nDown a quiet rural field or forest path, around the entrance of a village, I go to meet someone.\nEverything sinks into stillness, and at some point time seems to have stopped.\nA shabby village on the ridge of a hill: above tile roofs and walls that look about to crumble, white\nbillowing clouds are caught,\nand under the old tree at the back of the alley children played all day long.\nThat place is a memory from my childhood.\n'Wind' is the drifting cloud, the white billowing cloud that drifts wherever the wind blows; 'Light' is\na distant longing far past the present. To people who live without a moment to catch their breath\nin the desires of the everyday, the wind shows itself as wind,\nthe cloud shows itself as cloud, just like that.",
