    shopUrl: 'https://koreasmartcoop.cafe24.com/surl/O/89',
    title_en: 'Snow Field 02',
    description_en:
      'Just as countless warps and wefts cross to become cloth, dozens of layers of thread are stacked one upon another to complete my forest. Letting fine cotton thread build into tower after tower and form a forest demands a long patience. The work is hard and exhausting, but the joy of seeing thin lines come together into surfaces, and surfaces become a forest, is truly overwhelming. I draw and work with thread instead of paint. I chose thread as my material because it offers soft and rough textures and minute volumes that paint cannot express, and because countless changes in form can be pursued through delicate fingertip manipulation. Furthermore, thread carries a dual nature: it can be adjusted in brightness like paint, and it can be affixed and built into three dimensions like an object.\nThread is generally seen as a material for sewing or knitting, and its true value is recognized when it is woven into a fabric. But paradoxically I work with thread in its most fundamental and instinctive state, breaking the conventional frame and creating a new pictorial paradigm. The primal carries qualities both pure and mysterious. Seen from afar, my work resembles East Asian ink painting or watercolor, but up close one finds the layers of air and dimension held within the stacked threads, as well as a precise density and depth — a beauty and emotion that paint can never convey.\nI paint forests of nature. Nature, especially what may be called its essence — the forest — is, I believe, a passage that can correct our mistaken thoughts and values. For me, nature is not merely a subject to be reproduced but a sensory world that embraces all that exists between heaven and earth. And that world flows naturally into my work. Rather than concentrating on color or form, the principal elements of painting, I focus on expressing fundamental emotions — joy, sorrow, anger, longing, compassion, fate. What is wonderful is that those who view my work also sense these emotions of mine. In those moments I feel a connection, as though we are holding an invisible thread that links us without the need for words. Tolstoy said, "Art is a means of uniting people"; for me, the thread that is the medium of my work serves precisely as that medium, bringing person to person.',
    artist_en: 'Hong Jinhui',
    category: '회화',
