      '"To bring forth a single life is the same as to bring forth a single death."\nLife in the end has no choice but to meet its death,\nand the one who is the subject of my life, and the one who brings my life into being,\ncan only ever be a different person.\nThe weariness of having to live the life one did not bring forth oneself,\nthe anxiety of approaching death. The countless collisions, frustrations, and emptiness that arise in between.\nMy coming to observe purgatory—the place before life and death are decided—\nmay perhaps have been an inevitable process.\nFor me, who was searching for an alternative space\nin which one could exist freely, beyond the cycle of life and death,\npurgatory was a place that had always been beside me,\ncarried over from a far-off past life and the one before.',
