      '"To give birth to a life is the same as giving birth to a death."\nLife inevitably must meet death,\nand the self who is the subject of my own life,\nand the one who gave birth to my life,\nare necessarily different persons.\nThe weariness of having to live a life one did not bear oneself,\nthe anxiety of an approaching death — and the countless collisions, frustrations, and emptinesses that arise between them.\nMy coming to observe purgatory, the place before life and death are decided,\nmay have been an inevitable process.\nFor me — searching for an alternative space where I could exist freely,\noutside the cycle of life and death —\npurgatory was a place that had always been beside me,\ncontinuous from my distant past, from former lives and the lives before those.',
